<Requirements version="1" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-EXPL-1.1 Example  -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>System Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, upon power-up, perform an initialization sequence that includes: loading configuration parameters, initializing all sensors and actuators, initializing the motion control module, initializing the mapping and planning modules, and performing self-checks to determine whether all critical components are operational.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Mode Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide a mechanism to select and start the autonomous maze exploration mode, either automatically at startup or via an external input (e.g., button, UI command), and shall transition the control logic into exploration state when this mode is activated.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Real-Time Control Cycle</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall execute its main control loop, including sensor acquisition, state estimation, mapping updates, planning, and motion command generation, at a minimum frequency of 20 Hz while the robot is in motion.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Resource Utilization Limits</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The software shall limit its average CPU utilization to at most 80% and its RAM usage to within the available physical memory defined for the target platform, under nominal exploration operation, to ensure stable real-time behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1.5">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Logging Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide a logging subsystem that records key exploration events, including state transitions, fault detections, path planning decisions, and major mapping updates, with timestamps, to persistent or retrievable storage.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-EXPL-1.2 Explore Maze      -->
  <!-- ================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement an exploration state machine with at least the states "Idle", "Exploring", "Paused", "Error", and "Completed", and shall autonomously transition between these states based on events such as start command, fault detection, or exploration completion.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration Strategy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement an exploration strategy that identifies frontier cells or regions (boundaries between known free and unknown areas) in the internal maze representation and selects navigation goals toward these frontiers until no reachable frontier remains.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Goal Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.2.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, at each exploration step, select a next exploration goal cell or pose based on criteria including reachability, distance cost, and expected information gain, and shall provide this goal to the path planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Maze Coverage Completion Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
