    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall apply filtering or hysteresis in occupancy classification such that a single contradictory sensor reading does not immediately flip a cell’s classification between free and blocked without additional confirming evidence.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-MAP-2.3 Time Constraint      -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Monitoring</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start a mapping timer when exploration begins and shall continuously monitor the elapsed time during exploration.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.3.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Limit Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall treat the mapping as complete and transition the exploration state machine to "Completed" when the elapsed mapping time reaches 5 minutes, even if unknown cells remain.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-PLAN-3.1 Path Planning       -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement a grid-based path planning algorithm, such as A* or Dijkstra, that computes collision-free paths over free cells in the internal maze representation between a given start cell and target cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Optimal Path Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The planner shall compute paths that minimize total travel cost, where cost is defined primarily as the total path length measured in number of cell transitions or metric distance.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall be able to recompute a path when the map is updated in a way that invalidates the current path, such as newly discovered blocked cells on the planned route.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Time Bound</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ensure that individual path planning computations for typical maze sizes up to 32 by 32 cells complete within 200 milliseconds under nominal load.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-RUN-4.1 Return to Start      -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
