<Requirements version="2" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- ========================= -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-EXPL-1.1 Example  -->
  <!-- Clarified intent per Finding LLR--1--27 -->
  <!-- ========================= -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Autonomous Exploration Mode</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide an autonomous exploration operating mode that, when activated, initializes required components, executes a continuous control loop, and records operational data while the robot explores the maze without manual control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>System Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-SYS-1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, upon power-up, perform an initialization sequence that includes loading configuration parameters, initializing all sensors and actuators, initializing the motion control, mapping, planning, and logging modules, and performing self-checks to determine whether all critical components are operational.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Mode Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-SYS-1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall provide a mechanism to select and start the autonomous maze exploration mode, either automatically at startup or via an external input, and shall transition the global control logic into the exploration mode when this mode is activated.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Main Control Loop Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-6.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-7.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall execute a main control loop during autonomous exploration that, in each cycle, performs at least sensor acquisition, state estimation, map update, path planning or selection, collision avoidance, and motion command generation while the robot is in motion.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.5">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Main Control Loop Frequency</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall execute the main control loop at a minimum frequency of 20 Hz while the robot is in motion.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.6">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Resource Utilization Limits</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, under nominal exploration operation, limit its average CPU utilization to at most 80 percent and its RAM usage to at most 64 megabytes on the target platform to ensure stable real-time behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-1.7">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Logging Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall record key exploration events, including operating mode transitions, fault detections, path planning decisions, and major mapping updates, with timestamps, to persistent or retrievable storage.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-EXPL-1.2 Explore Maze      -->
  <!-- ================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-SYS-1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement an exploration controller that manages at least the states Idle, Exploring, Paused, Error, and Completed, and shall autonomously transition between these states based on events such as start command, fault detection, mapping time limit reached, or exploration completion.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration Strategy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement an exploration strategy that identifies frontier cells or regions, defined as boundaries between known free and unknown areas in the internal maze representation, and selects navigation goals toward these frontiers until no reachable frontier remains.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Goal Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-2.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, at each exploration step, select a next exploration goal cell or pose based on criteria including reachability, estimated path cost, and expected information gain, and shall provide this goal to the path planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Maze Coverage Completion Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-3.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall determine that exploration of the maze is complete when all cells within the reachable area are classified as either free or blocked and no additional reachable unknown cells remain in the internal representation, or when the mapping time limit is reached.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Movement Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-7.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RELIAB-5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall command the robot to follow the paths produced by the planning module from the current position to selected exploration goals until the exploration completion criterion is met or an error condition is detected.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-2.6">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Progress Monitoring</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-3.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically, at least once per second during exploration, compute and record the current coverage ratio of explored cells versus reachable maze area to monitor exploration progress.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-EXPL-1.3 Wall Detection    -->
  <!-- ================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Raw Sensor Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall periodically acquire raw distance or proximity measurements from all wall-detection sensors defined in the sensor data interface description at a minimum frequency of 20 Hz while the robot is moving.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Presence Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-6.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall process sensor measurements to estimate the presence or absence of walls in the robot’s vicinity, including at least the four primary directions relative to the robot (front, back, left, right), and output discrete wall flags for use by mapping and collision avoidance.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Immediate Wall Avoidance Reaction</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-7.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall, upon detecting an imminent wall collision based on configured proximity thresholds, immediately generate and send actuator commands to decelerate or stop and, if necessary, execute an avoidance maneuver such as turning away from the wall.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-EXPL-3.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Detection Latency</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ensure that the time from a sensor detecting a wall within a configured safety distance to the issuance of a corresponding actuator command to reduce speed or stop does not exceed 100 milliseconds.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-MAP-2.1 Create Map           -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid-Based Map Representation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall maintain an internal two-dimensional grid-based representation of the maze, where each cell corresponds to a fixed-size region of the physical maze and stores at least its occupancy classification and whether it has been visited.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Coordinate Frame</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall define a consistent map coordinate frame with an origin at the starting cell of the robot and shall maintain a mapping between cell indices and physical positions in the maze.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Position Tracking for Mapping</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-INTERF-6.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall estimate the robot’s current pose, including position and orientation, within the map coordinate frame using available odometry and sensor data to enable consistent updates to the internal representation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Incremental Map Update</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.3</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall update the internal map cells incrementally during exploration based on the current robot pose and wall presence estimates, marking neighboring cells as blocked where walls are detected and as free where space is detected.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-2.5">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Map Storage Capacity</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall support storing at least a maze of 32 by 32 cells at the chosen cell resolution without exceeding the allocated memory for the mapping functionality.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-MAP-2.2 Cell Classification  -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Initial Unknown Classification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall initialize all cells in the internal maze representation to the classification unknown before exploration starts.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free and Blocked Classification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall classify cells as free if they are traversable based on sensor data and robot traversal history, and as blocked if they contain walls or obstacles according to wall presence estimation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Visited Cell Tracking</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall mark the map cell corresponding to the robot’s current pose as visited whenever the robot enters it, to support exploration coverage evaluation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-3.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Classification Consistency</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-3.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall apply filtering or hysteresis in occupancy classification such that a single contradictory sensor reading does not immediately change a cell’s classification between free and blocked without additional confirming evidence.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-MAP-2.3 Time Constraint      -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-4.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Monitoring</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-1.4</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall start a mapping timer when exploration begins and shall continuously monitor the elapsed time during exploration.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-MAP-4.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Mapping Time Limit Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-EXPL-2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall treat the mapping as complete and transition the exploration controller to the Completed state when the elapsed mapping time reaches 5 minutes, even if unknown cells remain.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- ===================================== -->
  <!-- HLR: HL-PLAN-3.1 Path Planning       -->
  <!-- ===================================== -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-MAP-2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement a grid-based path planning algorithm, such as A-star or Dijkstra, that computes collision-free paths over cells classified as free in the internal maze representation between a given start cell and target cell.
